article.headline: Air Force 75, Norfolk St. 52
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Anwar Johnson scored 17 points as Air Force defeated Norfolk State 75-52 Sunday to stop a two-game slide. Air Force (4-2) shot a season-high 51.1 percent from the field and had a 37-25 rebounding edge over Norfolk State (1-3), which made 39 percent of its shots from the field. The Falcons opened the second half with a 15-4 run to lead 53-24 with 14:24 remaining. Air Force went up 66-36 with 6:39 left in the game. Norfolk State never got closer than 20 points in the second half. Michael DeLoach had 16 points to lead Norfolk State in scoring.
